{
  "texts": [
    "It decomposes the Text-to-SQL task into 4 steps: schema linking; query Schema Linking includes ten randomly selected samples from the training set of the Spider dataset and follows the chain-of-thought template.",
    "The 10 examples are static at the prompt, that is, they are not randomly generated at run time.",
    "For the column names mentioned in the question, the corresponding columns and their tables are selected from the schema; possible entities and cell values are also extracted from the question.",
    "Furthermore, the prompt tends to be very large, and its length may increase significantly depending on the size of the database.",
    "In some cases, it might exceed the token limit imposed by the LLM."
  ]
}